
Ranger Help for: attract
========================

SYNTAX:      attract follower/attract <race> follower
USAGE:       primary terrain only
SLOT COST:   9
BASE SP:     variable
SKILL TYPE:  follower

SUMMARY:    
Once a Ranger gains this ability, he or she may attract a friend follower
from any room that has his or her primary terrain in it. Followers
come in all shapes and sizes, from ants to elephants. Some are smarter
than others, some are stronger than others. What comes out of the 
wilderness to aid you is dependent on what your primary terrain is. IE:
You won't get a seal if your primary terrain is desert. Once you attract
a follower, you will get the same one until it dies.

As you increase your level, its level will go up along side of you. Each
follower has a max level that it can achieve, which will affect things
such as fighting or carrying weight. Each follower is also rated on how
smart and trainable it is. All followers can learn at least one task, some
can learn two, and the smartest ones can learn three. Some tasks are too 
tough for some followers to learn as well. A list of tasks are:

Easy Tasks:        slay, burden and guard
Medium Tasks:      fetch, carry and obscure
Difficult Tasks:   explore, hunt and forage

Tasks are very handy, and helpful to a Ranger. For more detail on each
task, type 'rh <task name>' and 'rh teach'.

IMPORTANT NOTE:
Each Ranger has a set amount of followers that will come to his or her
aid over time that is determined at join time. Everytime a Ranger allows
a follower to die, you get one closer to that number. Once a Ranger has
let his or personal number of followers die, no followers will ever come
to the Ranger's aid again! And, if you teach a follower a task, and then
let it die, you will have to reteach it to the next follower if it is
capable of learning it. You are guaranteed at least 2 followers, but after
that be wary and take care of your follower. YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED.

